    "Hand gesture recognition proposed system Spiking neural networkIn this work, the utilization of the SCNN proposed in [1] is adopted with certain modifications to streamline the model and enhance its computational efficiency.",
    "The architecture of the modified SCNN model is illustrated in Fig. 6.",
    "Specifically, the three convolutional layers maintain identical kernel sizes, padding, and stride, preserving their characteristics from the original SCNN model.",
    "Equally, the fully connected (FC) layer with an input size of 64 is retained.",
    "To maintain consistent model performance during both training and inference, batch normalization layers are omitted after each convolutional layer due to their different behaviors in these two processes."
